{"title":"A theory of information, by Noah Smith","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/897759350/0/marginalrevolution~A-theory-of-information-by-Noah-Smith.html","date":1716793729000,"content":"<blockquote><p>So here you go: a theory of how totalitarianism might naturally triumph. The basic idea is that when information is costly, liberal democracy wins because it gathers more and better information than closed societies, but when information is cheap, negative-sum <em>information tournaments</em> sap an increasingly large portion of a liberal society’s resources. Remember that I don’t <em>believe</em> this theory; I’m merely trying to formulate it.</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/how-liberal-democracy-might-lose\" target=\"_blank\">the full blog post</a>, gated after some point.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/05/a-theory-of-information-by-noah-smith.html\">A theory of information, by Noah Smith</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/897759350/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/897759350/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/897759350/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/897759350/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/x.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/19/897759350/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/email20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https:/